      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ROX THE WORLD (8) is building in fitness and has the hoof on the till following back-to-back placings at this circuit and distance. Was runner-up from this barrier before a third from the back line last week, racing three wide without cover both times. Peaking now so with better luck he can break through. SAMMY SUFFARELL (9) draws wide but is in a purple patch of form. Raced parked when he scored at this circuit and distance two back then gave his opponents no chance last start when he cruised to a 15 metre victory at Pinjarra. With luck from the outside barrier he could strike again. RELLIM (3) should enjoy this barrier having come from there to place three back at this circuit and distance. TROIS FONTAINE (1) can be competitive from the ace draw.",
